1
00:01:38,519 --> 00:01:39,239
I promise

2
00:01:39,239 --> 00:01:40,560
you'll love this house.

3
00:01:41,159 --> 00:01:42,920
Hello, come on in.

4
00:01:43,239 --> 00:01:44,560
Li, welcome.

5
00:01:44,640 --> 00:01:45,640
- Get in.
- Thanks.

6
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:46,079
This way.

7
00:01:48,120 --> 00:01:49,120
Any other entrance?

8
00:01:50,680 --> 00:01:51,519
Over here, let's go.

9
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:55,040
I'm not short on cash.

10
00:01:55,439 --> 00:01:56,120
Sure, sure.

11
00:01:57,319 --> 00:01:58,799
We really want to sell it.

12
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:00,799
Everything's negotiable.

13
00:02:01,760 --> 00:02:02,519
This place

14
00:02:02,599 --> 00:02:04,040
once belonged to an artist.

15
00:02:04,640 --> 00:02:06,359
It's been kept in great shape.

16
00:02:06,359 --> 00:02:07,400
This way, Mr. Li.

17
00:02:07,760 --> 00:02:08,719
Let's check the living room.

18
00:02:26,080 --> 00:02:27,560
This is the living room, Mr. Li.

19
00:02:28,520 --> 00:02:29,280
Right, Mr. Li.

20
00:02:30,159 --> 00:02:30,919
Take a look.

21
00:02:31,159 --> 00:02:32,639
The overall style and decor.

22
00:02:34,879 --> 00:02:36,360
What a huge fish tank.

23
00:02:36,479 --> 00:02:37,639
But no silver arowanas in it?

24
00:02:38,120 --> 00:02:38,800
So tacky.

25
00:02:39,560 --> 00:02:41,360
I'll get you some

26
00:02:41,360 --> 00:02:42,080
fine ones later, Mr. Li.

27
00:02:44,120 --> 00:02:45,879
All furniture here is solid wood.

28
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:47,039
The style is

29
00:02:47,639 --> 00:02:49,479
stately, luxurious and elegant.

30
00:02:50,240 --> 00:02:50,719
Right.

31
00:02:50,919 --> 00:02:51,919
There's also a big courtyard out front.

32
00:02:52,159 --> 00:02:52,680
It's really grand.

33
00:02:52,680 --> 00:02:53,560
Come, I'll show you.

34
00:02:57,960 --> 00:02:58,520
Look.

35
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:02,560
Mr. Li,

36
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:03,800
this house

37
00:03:04,240 --> 00:03:05,199
has an extra top floor.

38
00:03:05,719 --> 00:03:07,599
4 bedrooms and 2 living rooms in total.

39
00:03:24,360 --> 00:03:25,199
Forgot to mention this.

40
00:03:25,199 --> 00:03:26,240
There's a bar counter here.

41
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:27,840
You can invite friends over

42
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:28,840
to enjoy red wine.

43
00:03:35,120 --> 00:03:36,159
Why's the power out here?

44
00:03:38,319 --> 00:03:39,719
We don't come here often.

45
00:03:39,719 --> 00:03:41,080
Could it be an unpaid bill?

46
00:03:41,639 --> 00:03:42,199
I don't think so.

47
00:03:42,199 --> 00:03:43,319
The fish tank light is still on.

48
00:03:43,599 --> 00:03:44,840
Must be a wiring issue.

49
00:03:44,960 --> 00:03:45,759
It's an old villa after all.

50
00:03:45,879 --> 00:03:46,960
Just flip the switch later.

51
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:03,439
This place feels spooky.

52
00:04:04,159 --> 00:04:05,439
I think I need

53
00:04:05,439 --> 00:04:06,080
a feng shui master

54
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:06,879
to check it out first.

55
00:04:06,879 --> 00:04:07,840
Wait, Mr. Li.

56
00:04:07,919 --> 00:04:09,520
The feng shui here is perfectly fine.

57
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:10,479
Absolutely fine.

58
00:04:14,520 --> 00:04:15,360
Someone's upstairs?

59
00:04:16,519 --> 00:04:17,240
Mrs. Lu.

60
00:04:17,920 --> 00:04:19,720
Anyone's upstairs?

61
00:04:20,079 --> 00:04:20,839
No one at all.

62
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:22,680
I checked upstairs just now.

63
00:04:22,879 --> 00:04:23,879
It's totally empty.

64
00:04:24,319 --> 00:04:24,959
That's right.

65
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:37,639
Oh, it must be

66
00:04:38,399 --> 00:04:39,720
air in the pipes.

67
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:41,120
We've all heard

68
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:42,560
marble dropping sounds at home, right?

69
00:04:43,079 --> 00:04:44,120
Don't try to fool me.

70
00:04:44,439 --> 00:04:45,240
What really happened

71
00:04:45,240 --> 00:04:46,160
to the previous owner?

72
00:04:46,519 --> 00:04:47,920
Nothing, just...

73
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:49,399
Forget it. I'm leaving.

74
00:04:49,399 --> 00:04:50,040
Wait, Mr. Li.

75
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:50,800
Mr. Li, hold on.

76
00:04:51,160 --> 00:04:51,879
Listen to me.

77
00:04:51,879 --> 00:04:53,000
Please wait.

78
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:53,600
Mr. Li.

79
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:04,600
Did you see these handprints

80
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:05,639
when you came in?

81
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:07,920
No, I didn't.

82
00:05:08,519 --> 00:05:09,279
Me neither.

83
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:12,040
Oh my god!

84
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:29,720
Isn't this our Picasso?

85
00:05:31,120 --> 00:05:32,399
And there was a Beethoven upstairs.

86
00:05:40,120 --> 00:05:40,959
Over here.

87
00:05:47,399 --> 00:05:49,000
Is this another art studio?

88
00:05:50,519 --> 00:05:52,199
These drawings are gorgeous.

89
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:53,639
Who drew them?

90
00:05:55,279 --> 00:05:56,079
I did.

91
00:05:57,439 --> 00:05:58,439
You?

92
00:05:59,839 --> 00:06:00,759
You can draw?

93
00:06:01,839 --> 00:06:02,439
So what?

94
00:06:03,720 --> 00:06:04,959
I've got nice hands,

95
00:06:05,120 --> 00:06:06,199
so why can't I draw well?

96
00:06:08,920 --> 00:06:10,000
If that's the case,

97
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:11,120
I look good,

98
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:12,480
so my handwriting must be nice too.

99
00:06:13,319 --> 00:06:14,680
I think you look better playing ghost.

100
00:06:21,720 --> 00:06:23,199
Is this the albinism tree?

101
00:06:24,319 --> 00:06:25,360
Did you draw that too?

102
00:06:27,519 --> 00:06:28,439
Just a casual sketch.

103
00:06:38,439 --> 00:06:39,199
I noticed there are

104
00:06:39,279 --> 00:06:41,160
drawings in the studio upstairs.

105
00:06:42,160 --> 00:06:43,360
Are those also yours?

106
00:06:51,639 --> 00:06:53,120
There should be four drawings, right?

107
00:06:53,120 --> 00:06:54,160
One is missing.

108
00:06:54,160 --> 00:06:55,120
You went into that room?

109
00:06:56,079 --> 00:06:57,519
When we split up,

110
00:06:57,519 --> 00:06:58,279
I popped in for a look.

111
00:06:58,279 --> 00:06:59,240
Who told you to go in?

112
00:07:03,480 --> 00:07:04,120
I didn't mean to.

113
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:05,439
Who let you go in?

114
00:07:13,839 --> 00:07:14,399
Off you go.

115
00:07:20,560 --> 00:07:21,319
I'm sorry.

116
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:23,680
I didn't mean to.

117
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:32,839
I'll head back now.

118
00:08:00,319 --> 00:08:01,079
Zhou Wan.

119
00:08:03,560 --> 00:08:04,600
What a surprise.

120
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:16,199
We had an agreement,

121
00:08:16,199 --> 00:08:17,600
didn't we?

122
00:08:19,639 --> 00:08:21,279
You stay out of my life,

123
00:08:22,399 --> 00:08:23,680
and I'll pay for Grandma's treatment.

124
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:26,519
Is that right?

125
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:33,480
Answer me.

126
00:08:38,720 --> 00:08:39,399
Yes.

127
00:08:43,120 --> 00:08:43,720
Yes?

128
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:47,519
Then what are you doing?

129
00:08:49,639 --> 00:08:50,399
Playing games with me?

130
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:55,039
Lu Xixiao and I are just friends.

131
00:08:58,320 --> 00:08:59,679
I won't tell him

132
00:09:00,360 --> 00:09:01,840
about you and me.

133
00:09:07,039 --> 00:09:08,159
By the way,

134
00:09:08,799 --> 00:09:09,919
how did your exam go?

135
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:15,039
I didn't take it.

136
00:09:16,919 --> 00:09:17,840
You didn't take it?

137
00:09:20,679 --> 00:09:22,000
Grandma passed out that day.

138
00:09:23,120 --> 00:09:24,799
Uremia triggered a heart attack.

139
00:09:28,919 --> 00:09:30,159
Honestly,

140
00:09:31,039 --> 00:09:32,080
you and your grandma

141
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:33,840
have had tough luck.

142
00:09:37,360 --> 00:09:38,559
Do you want her treated?

143
00:09:39,399 --> 00:09:40,480
I can help you.

144
00:09:43,519 --> 00:09:44,320
But

145
00:09:46,240 --> 00:09:47,360
you have to

146
00:09:48,519 --> 00:09:49,919
keep our promise.

147
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:52,279
Stay away

148
00:09:52,279 --> 00:09:53,320
from Lu Xixiao.

149
00:09:53,720 --> 00:09:54,360
Deal?

150
00:09:55,840 --> 00:09:57,480
There's really nothing between us.

151
00:10:00,039 --> 00:10:00,720
Besides,

152
00:10:03,120 --> 00:10:04,519
you took all dad's

153
00:10:04,519 --> 00:10:05,039
insurance money...

154
00:10:05,039 --> 00:10:06,159
That money

155
00:10:06,159 --> 00:10:07,639
was meant for me.

156
00:10:11,159 --> 00:10:13,120
It's marital joint property.

157
00:10:13,399 --> 00:10:15,879
I'm the beneficiary, not you.

158
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:17,840
Get it?

159
00:10:27,519 --> 00:10:28,720
I'll count grandma's medical bills

160
00:10:31,240 --> 00:10:32,600
as a loan from you.

161
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:34,279
I will pay you back.

162
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:39,799
Here.

163
00:10:45,279 --> 00:10:45,960
This money

164
00:10:45,960 --> 00:10:47,399
is for you.

165
00:10:49,240 --> 00:10:51,159
But don't push my patience

166
00:10:51,720 --> 00:10:53,399
like this.

167
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:21,879
Can I trust you?

168
00:12:14,960 --> 00:12:15,840
Delete him on WeChat.

169
00:12:45,320 --> 00:12:46,279
The cake's good.

170
00:12:46,960 --> 00:12:47,919
Have some.

171
00:12:55,039 --> 00:12:56,440
I'm sorry, Lu Xixiao.

172
00:12:57,159 --> 00:12:58,360
To save Grandma,

173
00:12:59,080 --> 00:13:00,200
I have no other choice.

174
00:13:03,399 --> 00:13:04,799
I didn't

175
00:13:06,320 --> 00:13:07,480
mean to.

176
00:13:30,039 --> 00:13:31,159
You two are so selfish.

177
00:13:31,440 --> 00:13:32,799
You've torn this family apart.

178
00:13:33,639 --> 00:13:34,399
Don't you know only

179
00:13:34,759 --> 00:13:36,080
harmony brings prosperity?

180
00:13:36,960 --> 00:13:38,360
Dad, calm down.

181
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:40,159
Please don't be angry.

182
00:13:40,159 --> 00:13:40,559
If I

183
00:13:40,559 --> 00:13:41,919
hadn't done this,

184
00:13:41,919 --> 00:13:43,399
would he ever come back?

185
00:13:45,799 --> 00:13:46,559
Grandpa.

186
00:13:50,279 --> 00:13:52,120
Finally show up?

187
00:13:53,919 --> 00:13:54,879
I was wrong.

188
00:13:54,879 --> 00:13:56,320
Well? What did you do wrong?

189
00:13:58,840 --> 00:14:00,240
I shouldn't

190
00:14:00,519 --> 00:14:02,519
have come back at all.

191
00:14:03,480 --> 00:14:04,399
I should've texted you

192
00:14:04,399 --> 00:14:05,440
after landing.

193
00:14:10,519 --> 00:14:12,000
It's just a family dispute.

194
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:12,759
No big deal.

195
00:14:13,440 --> 00:14:14,360
Don't worry.

196
00:14:14,679 --> 00:14:16,360
I'll always stand by you.

197
00:14:18,320 --> 00:14:19,639
I have your support, Grandpa,

198
00:14:20,639 --> 00:14:21,360
but not

199
00:14:21,360 --> 00:14:22,240
everyone's.

200
00:14:23,879 --> 00:14:26,200
You left without a word.

201
00:14:26,759 --> 00:14:28,440
How can you expect others to back you?

202
00:14:30,919 --> 00:14:31,559
Grandpa.

203
00:14:33,320 --> 00:14:34,399
I need a word with him.

204
00:14:39,720 --> 00:14:41,279
Dad, let me walk you out.

205
00:14:44,559 --> 00:14:45,639
Listen up.

206
00:14:46,159 --> 00:14:47,320
No one touches

207
00:14:47,320 --> 00:14:48,759
Shen Lan's house.

208
00:14:50,159 --> 00:14:51,000
Understood.

209
00:14:51,240 --> 00:14:52,399
It's my fault.

210
00:14:52,519 --> 00:14:53,519
Won't happen again.

211
00:14:54,440 --> 00:14:55,519
Shen Lan is Shen Lan.

212
00:14:55,679 --> 00:14:56,399
You are you.

213
00:14:56,879 --> 00:14:58,120
You two are nothing alike.

214
00:14:58,360 --> 00:15:00,320
Right. I got it wrong.

215
00:15:02,480 --> 00:15:03,720
Why bring the drawings back?

216
00:15:05,600 --> 00:15:06,879
The Everpeak Group's

217
00:15:06,879 --> 00:15:08,519
celebrating its 40th anniversary soon.

218
00:15:08,879 --> 00:15:10,279
We'll host a banquet.

219
00:15:11,399 --> 00:15:13,279
And many business partners will come.

220
00:15:14,080 --> 00:15:15,840
Quite the devoted husband act, Mr. Lu.

221
00:15:16,519 --> 00:15:17,879
You get better at it every year.

222
00:15:18,799 --> 00:15:19,600
Quit your

223
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:20,799
sarcasm.

224
00:15:20,799 --> 00:15:21,480
Listen to me.

225
00:15:21,480 --> 00:15:24,039
You have to be there that day.

226
00:15:24,039 --> 00:15:25,000
That's why

227
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:26,200
I let you come back.

228
00:15:26,320 --> 00:15:27,000
Understand?

229
00:15:27,720 --> 00:15:29,000
You never asked me

230
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:30,000
to show up before.

231
00:15:31,559 --> 00:15:32,720
You owe an apology

232
00:15:33,320 --> 00:15:34,559
to Mr. He's son.

233
00:15:39,159 --> 00:15:39,840
Which Mr. He?

234
00:15:41,559 --> 00:15:42,480
Don't play dumb

235
00:15:42,480 --> 00:15:43,320
with me.

236
00:15:43,440 --> 00:15:44,960
Apologize properly.

237
00:15:48,240 --> 00:15:50,279
Fine. But I have one condition.

238
00:15:51,039 --> 00:15:51,919
A condition?

239
00:15:52,720 --> 00:15:53,919
How dare you?

240
00:15:53,919 --> 00:15:54,919
Leave my mom's house alone.

241
00:15:56,919 --> 00:15:57,759
I never planned to

242
00:15:57,759 --> 00:15:59,240
sell it anyway.

243
00:16:00,559 --> 00:16:02,120
As for your overseas study,

244
00:16:02,960 --> 00:16:04,159
it's your future we're talking about.

245
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:06,000
As your father,

246
00:16:06,440 --> 00:16:08,039
I have to look out for you.

247
00:17:21,440 --> 00:17:22,720
Your dad's insurance money

248
00:17:22,720 --> 00:17:23,960
was meant for me.

249
00:17:24,640 --> 00:17:26,519
It's marital shared property.

250
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:32,160
Honestly,

251
00:17:33,119 --> 00:17:34,039
you and your grandma

252
00:17:35,160 --> 00:17:36,079
have had tough luck.

253
00:18:46,640 --> 00:18:47,839
Anniversary banquet?

254
00:18:49,640 --> 00:18:51,799
Core members of the Lu family will attend...

255
00:18:53,720 --> 00:18:55,119
She'll definitely come

256
00:18:55,240 --> 00:18:56,319
to such an important banquet.

257
00:18:56,799 --> 00:18:57,599
This is my only chance

258
00:18:57,599 --> 00:18:59,039
to save grandma.

259
00:19:05,160 --> 00:19:05,839
I'm sorry.

260
00:19:06,319 --> 00:19:08,119
I'll tell you everything someday.

261
00:19:08,880 --> 00:19:09,960
But until then,

262
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:11,680
I'll make her pay back

263
00:19:12,039 --> 00:19:13,079
what she owes me.

264
00:19:19,519 --> 00:19:21,000
If his rank gets overtaken,

265
00:19:21,480 --> 00:19:22,759
he won't sleep a wink.

266
00:19:23,279 --> 00:19:24,599
He's just that petty.

267
00:19:53,119 --> 00:19:53,839
What?

268
00:19:53,839 --> 00:19:55,119
Just take back first place.

269
00:19:58,240 --> 00:19:59,000
Come on.

270
00:19:59,319 --> 00:20:00,599
She helped you prank others,

271
00:20:00,599 --> 00:20:02,000
yet you pushed her away right after.

272
00:20:02,160 --> 00:20:03,079
No wonder she deleted you.

273
00:20:04,519 --> 00:20:05,759
She already gave you an out.

274
00:20:05,759 --> 00:20:06,559
Can't you see that?

275
00:20:07,079 --> 00:20:08,160
I see it.

276
00:20:08,359 --> 00:20:09,000
So what?

277
00:20:09,519 --> 00:20:11,519
I decide when to back down, not her.

278
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:14,079
Come on.

279
00:20:14,400 --> 00:20:15,480
I already set the stage for you.

280
00:20:15,480 --> 00:20:16,519
Talk nicely, okay?

281
00:20:16,720 --> 00:20:17,920
Save your efforts.

282
00:20:18,559 --> 00:20:20,319
You must be tired. Water?

283
00:20:22,119 --> 00:20:22,799
Where are you going?

284
00:20:22,799 --> 00:20:23,680
None of your business.

285
00:20:28,720 --> 00:20:29,759
I'm thirsty.

286
00:20:31,880 --> 00:20:32,599
Thanks.

287
00:20:34,519 --> 00:20:35,880
Both of you are so stubborn.

288
00:20:36,319 --> 00:20:37,079
I give up.

289
00:20:43,599 --> 00:20:44,759
You can barely take care of yourself.

290
00:20:44,759 --> 00:20:45,920
Why treat me to a meal?

291
00:20:46,519 --> 00:20:47,559
I still owe you

292
00:20:47,559 --> 00:20:48,720
for the scooter.

293
00:20:49,079 --> 00:20:50,359
I can definitely afford

294
00:20:50,359 --> 00:20:51,200
afternoon tea.

295
00:20:51,519 --> 00:20:52,519
Just enjoy it.

296
00:20:52,519 --> 00:20:53,240
Okay?

297
00:20:53,599 --> 00:20:54,759
Generous of you, Miss Zhou.

298
00:20:56,720 --> 00:20:57,680
Besides,

299
00:20:58,440 --> 00:20:59,960
I need to ask you something.

300
00:21:00,960 --> 00:21:01,799
I knew it.

301
00:21:02,359 --> 00:21:03,759
You never do something for nothing.

302
00:21:03,759 --> 00:21:04,160
This meal

303
00:21:04,160 --> 00:21:05,200
isn't just a simple treat.

304
00:21:06,119 --> 00:21:06,720
What's your question?

305
00:21:08,359 --> 00:21:10,400
When would

306
00:21:10,400 --> 00:21:11,240
a guy

307
00:21:11,240 --> 00:21:12,319
bring a girl home?

308
00:21:15,599 --> 00:21:16,920
Who are you going home with?

309
00:21:17,599 --> 00:21:18,279
Lu Xixiao.

310
00:21:18,640 --> 00:21:19,400
Do you like him?

311
00:21:19,640 --> 00:21:20,279
No.

312
00:21:20,279 --> 00:21:21,440
Then why go to his place?

313
00:21:22,119 --> 00:21:22,960
I need to talk to him.

314
00:21:22,960 --> 00:21:23,519
About what?

315
00:21:25,960 --> 00:21:27,240
Can I keep it to myself for now?

316
00:21:27,240 --> 00:21:28,039
Boring.

317
00:21:29,200 --> 00:21:30,240
You two know each other.

318
00:21:30,240 --> 00:21:31,279
Just talk to him directly.

319
00:21:35,559 --> 00:21:37,160
We had a fight.

320
00:21:37,839 --> 00:21:38,960
I deleted his WeChat.

321
00:21:39,920 --> 00:21:40,599
And?

322
00:21:42,079 --> 00:21:43,039
I tried to speak to him

323
00:21:43,039 --> 00:21:43,880
at the arcade,

324
00:21:44,759 --> 00:21:46,240
but he ignored me completely

325
00:21:46,359 --> 00:21:47,279
and left.

326
00:21:48,279 --> 00:21:49,160
That's pretty cold.

327
00:21:49,920 --> 00:21:50,920
Yeah.

328
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:53,839
Let me think.

329
00:21:56,960 --> 00:21:57,839
Take it easy.

330
00:22:04,480 --> 00:22:05,359
I have an idea.

331
00:22:05,720 --> 00:22:07,119
But you have to be okay with it.

332
00:22:07,839 --> 00:22:08,680
What is it?

333
00:22:13,079 --> 00:22:15,559
Swallow your pride.

334
00:22:17,839 --> 00:22:19,400
First, add him back.

335
00:22:19,720 --> 00:22:21,119
Aren't you off to work this afternoon?

336
00:22:21,400 --> 00:22:22,640
Just do as I say.

337
00:22:27,839 --> 00:22:28,440
Our shop's running

338
00:22:28,440 --> 00:22:29,680
a promo right now.

339
00:22:29,880 --> 00:22:30,480
If you're interested,

340
00:22:30,480 --> 00:22:31,279
you can add me on WeChat.

341
00:22:38,799 --> 00:22:39,519
No need.

342
00:22:41,599 --> 00:22:43,480
Well, I'll add you.

343
00:22:44,160 --> 00:22:45,839
Such a snob.

344
00:22:46,079 --> 00:22:47,440
We need to approach this indirectly.

345
00:22:49,519 --> 00:22:51,119
I don't understand.

346
00:22:51,839 --> 00:22:53,119
Jiang Fan.

347
00:22:53,720 --> 00:22:54,240
That guy

348
00:22:54,240 --> 00:22:55,519
comes to the shop every day.

349
00:22:55,720 --> 00:22:57,240
He can be useful for once.

350
00:22:58,400 --> 00:23:00,519
You mean ask Jiang Fan for help?

351
00:23:01,880 --> 00:23:03,200
Since when are you two so close?

352
00:23:04,480 --> 00:23:05,119
That doesn't matter.

353
00:23:05,680 --> 00:23:07,440
He's at my uncle's shop every day.

354
00:23:07,599 --> 00:23:08,480
I'll just ask him.

355
00:23:10,680 --> 00:23:11,359
Hey.

356
00:23:11,480 --> 00:23:13,240
Wan and I brought

357
00:23:13,240 --> 00:23:14,000
some noodles for you.

358
00:23:15,480 --> 00:23:16,400
See? Xixiao.

359
00:23:16,519 --> 00:23:18,119
It's three-delicacy noodles.

360
00:23:18,319 --> 00:23:18,839
Didn't you say

361
00:23:18,839 --> 00:23:19,759
you were craving these?

362
00:23:20,240 --> 00:23:21,279
Miss Zhou sure knows you well.

363
00:23:21,279 --> 00:23:22,119
Not hungry.

364
00:23:24,319 --> 00:23:24,880
You,

365
00:23:25,319 --> 00:23:26,440
try tipping her off again,

366
00:23:26,440 --> 00:23:27,079
and you'll see.

367
00:23:30,200 --> 00:23:31,480
Who made such a mess on the floor?

368
00:23:32,960 --> 00:23:33,680
Who did it?

369
00:23:36,240 --> 00:23:37,119
He won't eat, I will.

370
00:23:37,519 --> 00:23:38,440
Give it here. I'm starving.

371
00:23:38,880 --> 00:23:39,920
Save me some.

372
00:23:39,920 --> 00:23:40,599
Stop it.

373
00:23:41,359 --> 00:23:42,480
Being such a jerk?

374
00:23:42,599 --> 00:23:43,759
One punch and he'd behave.

375
00:23:45,359 --> 00:23:47,039
Shh, shh, keep it down.

376
00:23:47,680 --> 00:23:48,680
What can I do?

377
00:23:48,920 --> 00:23:50,039
I'm the one who needs him.

378
00:23:53,319 --> 00:23:54,599
I've got another idea.

379
00:23:55,319 --> 00:23:56,640
Play the vulnerable card.

380
00:24:14,920 --> 00:24:16,039
Alright, that's enough.

381
00:24:18,039 --> 00:24:19,200
She's been working overtime for days.

382
00:24:19,480 --> 00:24:20,680
She even swapped shifts just for...

383
00:24:20,680 --> 00:24:21,359
For what?

384
00:24:24,240 --> 00:24:24,960
Feeling sorry for her?

385
00:24:26,119 --> 00:24:26,960
Then you take her shift.

386
00:24:30,960 --> 00:24:32,200
Nah.

387
00:24:32,440 --> 00:24:33,359
I'm tired.

388
00:24:45,799 --> 00:24:47,400
You really have a cold heart.

389
00:24:47,599 --> 00:24:48,799
Me? Cold-hearted?

390
00:24:52,119 --> 00:24:53,200
I lent you my bike for a few days,

391
00:24:54,839 --> 00:24:55,920
and now the rearview mirror is broken.

392
00:24:55,920 --> 00:24:56,680
Am I the cold one?

393
00:24:57,319 --> 00:24:59,039
Xixiao, loads of girls like you.

394
00:24:59,039 --> 00:25:00,200
The line would stretch all the way

395
00:25:00,200 --> 00:25:01,160
from the school gate to the classroom.

396
00:25:01,359 --> 00:25:02,799
Can't you see how she feels?

397
00:25:03,319 --> 00:25:04,160
She has done

398
00:25:04,160 --> 00:25:05,079
everything she can.

399
00:25:05,519 --> 00:25:06,319
Stop pretending.

400
00:25:06,640 --> 00:25:07,680
She's the one pretending.

401
00:25:08,519 --> 00:25:09,960
You want to see her too, don't you?

402
00:25:10,079 --> 00:25:11,160
Otherwise why go to the arcade

403
00:25:11,160 --> 00:25:11,799
every day?

404
00:25:11,920 --> 00:25:12,880
You never used to be

405
00:25:12,880 --> 00:25:13,519
this into games.

406
00:25:13,799 --> 00:25:15,279
No idea why you're being so stubborn.

407
00:25:15,720 --> 00:25:17,079
Enough, Jiang Fan.

408
00:25:18,480 --> 00:25:20,039
Fine, fine. I'm done.

409
00:25:20,400 --> 00:25:21,359
I'm done, okay?

410
00:25:21,599 --> 00:25:22,839
You've stayed,

411
00:25:23,920 --> 00:25:25,400
but now you're all moody.

412
00:25:26,519 --> 00:25:27,640
You even lost your bike.

413
00:25:27,880 --> 00:25:28,799
I wish you hadn't stayed at all.

414
00:25:28,799 --> 00:25:30,400
Good thing I stayed.

415
00:25:30,880 --> 00:25:31,440
Look what you did

416
00:25:31,440 --> 00:25:32,319
to my bike.

417
00:25:35,640 --> 00:25:36,319
You're still

418
00:25:36,319 --> 00:25:37,400
gonna ride it later,

419
00:25:37,519 --> 00:25:37,920
so...

420
00:25:37,920 --> 00:25:38,920
In your dreams.

421
00:25:39,039 --> 00:25:40,000
Hey.

422
00:25:40,160 --> 00:25:41,799
I'm getting off work.

423
00:25:42,119 --> 00:25:43,240
You're off this early?

424
00:25:44,440 --> 00:25:45,839
Uncle, bye.

425
00:25:46,319 --> 00:25:46,920
Now you

426
00:25:46,920 --> 00:25:48,240
call me uncle, huh?

427
00:25:49,519 --> 00:25:50,559
Be safe on the road.

428
00:25:51,519 --> 00:25:52,240
Alright, Xixiao,

429
00:25:52,480 --> 00:25:53,000
the bike's fixed.

430
00:25:53,000 --> 00:25:53,839
Check it out.

431
00:25:54,480 --> 00:25:56,240
Check it? I fixed it.

432
00:25:56,519 --> 00:25:57,440
You didn't even touch it.

433
00:25:57,920 --> 00:25:58,400
I...

434
00:25:58,519 --> 00:25:59,720
You used my tools.

435
00:26:02,519 --> 00:26:03,839
Since you're so attached,

436
00:26:03,839 --> 00:26:05,039
and you're good at repairing bikes.

437
00:26:05,400 --> 00:26:06,279
Why not stay?

438
00:26:06,279 --> 00:26:07,200
Work with me fixing bikes.

439
00:26:08,279 --> 00:26:09,640
He's got way more on his mind than that.

440
00:26:23,400 --> 00:26:24,119
Grandma.

441
00:26:24,519 --> 00:26:25,200
I'm here to see you.

442
00:26:25,480 --> 00:26:26,119
Good boy.

443
00:26:26,119 --> 00:26:27,079
What are you listening to?

444
00:26:27,599 --> 00:26:29,519
A group called The Phonograph.

445
00:26:29,599 --> 00:26:30,720
Wanna join?

446
00:26:30,880 --> 00:26:32,000
Let him be.

447
00:26:32,000 --> 00:26:32,799
Just enjoy your own music.

448
00:26:33,519 --> 00:26:34,480
I told you there's no need

449
00:26:34,480 --> 00:26:35,799
to come all this way to see us.

450
00:26:36,319 --> 00:26:37,519
Grandma's doing much better now.

451
00:26:37,920 --> 00:26:38,799
If you don't let me help,

452
00:26:38,799 --> 00:26:39,759
I'll be more worried.

453
00:26:40,480 --> 00:26:41,839
I was afraid

454
00:26:42,119 --> 00:26:43,680
you were still mad about last time.

455
00:26:45,200 --> 00:26:45,960
Let's talk outside.

456
00:26:46,119 --> 00:26:46,640
Okay.

457
00:26:51,039 --> 00:26:51,799
These are

458
00:26:51,799 --> 00:26:54,119
materials and admission brochures

459
00:26:54,240 --> 00:26:54,920
for local colleges

460
00:26:54,920 --> 00:26:55,839
in Pingchuan.

461
00:26:56,079 --> 00:26:56,880
Take a look.

462
00:26:58,079 --> 00:26:58,720
What now?

463
00:26:59,119 --> 00:27:00,039
You don't want us to apply to

464
00:27:00,039 --> 00:27:00,920
Huaqing together anymore?

465
00:27:02,200 --> 00:27:04,480
I still do,

466
00:27:05,799 --> 00:27:06,519
but

467
00:27:08,519 --> 00:27:09,720
your future is yours to decide.

468
00:27:13,079 --> 00:27:13,720
Thanks.

469
00:27:17,720 --> 00:27:19,119
Your birthday is coming up soon.

470
00:27:19,720 --> 00:27:20,799
Got any plans?

471
00:27:23,680 --> 00:27:24,519
Same as usual.

472
00:27:26,480 --> 00:27:27,119
Okay.

473
00:27:31,119 --> 00:27:32,319
Play properly.

474
00:27:32,319 --> 00:27:33,400
How are we gonna beat the record like this?

475
00:27:36,279 --> 00:27:36,960
Get more tokens.

476
00:27:39,720 --> 00:27:40,440
I'm out of coins.

477
00:27:41,519 --> 00:27:42,359
How come?

478
00:27:42,359 --> 00:27:43,599
You used them all up.

479
00:27:48,599 --> 00:27:49,279
Let's go.

480
00:27:54,759 --> 00:27:55,839
Zhou Wan isn't here.

481
00:28:01,799 --> 00:28:03,799
Even studying wasn't this hard.

482
00:28:04,599 --> 00:28:05,680
He's so stubborn,

483
00:28:05,680 --> 00:28:06,400
won't budge an inch.

484
00:28:07,680 --> 00:28:10,039
He clearly cares about you though.

485
00:28:12,079 --> 00:28:13,279
Whose side are you on anyway?

486
00:28:13,680 --> 00:28:14,319
He's so stubborn,

487
00:28:14,640 --> 00:28:16,160
won't budge an inch.

488
00:28:16,160 --> 00:28:16,839
Forget him.

489
00:28:17,559 --> 00:28:18,200
Enjoy the music.

490
00:28:23,000 --> 00:28:23,680
Give me your phone.

491
00:28:24,319 --> 00:28:25,000
What for?

492
00:28:25,400 --> 00:28:26,680
We have no coins left. Why take my phone?

493
00:28:26,680 --> 00:28:27,559
Don't ask too much.

494
00:28:32,119 --> 00:28:35,319
Just like this.

495
00:28:35,319 --> 00:28:36,960
When, where?

496
00:28:36,960 --> 00:28:38,799
Never ignorant,

497
00:28:38,799 --> 00:28:40,559
never craving.

498
00:28:40,559 --> 00:28:42,559
In this boundless world,

499
00:28:42,559 --> 00:28:44,160
I come, I go.

500
00:28:44,400 --> 00:28:45,079
Hello?

501
00:28:45,799 --> 00:28:46,920
Giving up already?

502
00:28:48,160 --> 00:28:49,519
Told you so.

503
00:28:49,920 --> 00:28:52,119
Alright.

504
00:28:52,119 --> 00:28:53,000
Let's keep going.

505
00:28:53,599 --> 00:28:54,480
Everyone join in!

506
00:28:54,480 --> 00:28:57,039
Lu Xixiao, stop pretending.

507
00:28:59,119 --> 00:29:00,599
It worked.

508
00:29:01,400 --> 00:29:02,240
What's happening?

509
00:29:02,240 --> 00:29:03,359
Give yourselves a round of applause.

510
00:29:06,279 --> 00:29:07,480
Hands up everyone!

511
00:29:17,759 --> 00:29:18,319
Zhou Wan.

512
00:29:19,519 --> 00:29:20,240
What are you doing here?

513
00:29:20,359 --> 00:29:21,119
We're closed.

514
00:29:21,119 --> 00:29:21,720
Just passing by.

515
00:29:22,440 --> 00:29:23,839
I'm off then.

516
00:29:24,920 --> 00:29:26,119
Bye, bye.

517
00:29:36,519 --> 00:29:37,119
Looking for me?

518
00:29:42,400 --> 00:29:43,440
Didn't know

519
00:29:44,519 --> 00:29:45,759
you're actually good at games.

520
00:29:51,279 --> 00:29:51,960
Just so-so.

521
00:29:56,400 --> 00:29:57,200
Stop pretending.

522
00:29:58,680 --> 00:29:59,480
Did you corner me here

523
00:29:59,480 --> 00:30:00,559
just to

524
00:30:01,640 --> 00:30:03,000
get on my nerves?

525
00:30:12,279 --> 00:30:13,880
I thought you didn't want to talk to me.

526
00:30:25,400 --> 00:30:26,480
I actually wanted to say

527
00:30:26,480 --> 00:30:27,160
I was wrong too that day.

528
00:30:28,319 --> 00:30:29,400
But you deleted me.

529
00:30:32,720 --> 00:30:33,680
What did you say?

530
00:30:38,200 --> 00:30:40,119
I said, I was wrong too.

531
00:30:42,079 --> 00:30:43,400
I lost my temper and

532
00:30:43,839 --> 00:30:44,680
shouldn't have spoken harshly to you.

533
00:30:46,359 --> 00:30:47,559
But still, no matter what,

534
00:30:48,400 --> 00:30:49,279
I don't think our relationship

535
00:30:49,279 --> 00:30:49,839
is at the point of

536
00:30:49,839 --> 00:30:51,000
cutting each other off.

537
00:30:56,240 --> 00:30:57,359
What relationship?

538
00:31:05,799 --> 00:31:06,480
Teacher-student.

539
00:31:11,920 --> 00:31:12,599
Friends.

540
00:31:13,880 --> 00:31:15,559
Fish-saving partners.

541
00:31:16,079 --> 00:31:16,960
Ghost partners.

542
00:31:17,880 --> 00:31:18,960
You still remember all that?

543
00:31:19,119 --> 00:31:20,000
My memory isn't that bad.

544
00:31:20,000 --> 00:31:20,519
Okay?

545
00:31:31,319 --> 00:31:32,400
So

546
00:31:34,039 --> 00:31:34,920
just...

547
00:31:36,480 --> 00:31:37,599
Add me back, okay?

548
00:31:40,359 --> 00:31:41,000
Pardon?

549
00:31:43,279 --> 00:31:44,319
Add me back.

550
00:31:54,400 --> 00:31:55,279
Mr. Bow.

551
00:32:00,440 --> 00:32:01,279
One more round.

552
00:32:05,200 --> 00:32:06,079
You think I'll play

553
00:32:06,079 --> 00:32:06,960
just because you asked?

554
00:32:17,480 --> 00:32:18,559
Noob.

555
00:32:21,519 --> 00:32:22,519
Bring it on.

556
00:32:53,079 --> 00:32:53,920
Yes!

557
00:32:54,839 --> 00:32:55,440
I won.

558
00:32:55,440 --> 00:32:56,640
We won.

559
00:32:57,240 --> 00:32:57,880
Fine.

560
00:32:58,759 --> 00:33:00,079
You can tag along.

561
00:33:00,720 --> 00:33:01,720
I took a bullet

562
00:33:01,720 --> 00:33:02,759
for you.

563
00:33:02,920 --> 00:33:04,000
How are you gonna thank me?

564
00:33:05,920 --> 00:33:07,039
What do you want me to do?

565
00:33:18,599 --> 00:33:21,160
Heard there's a band

566
00:33:21,240 --> 00:33:22,480
performing at your banquet.

567
00:33:23,599 --> 00:33:26,160
I'm a big fan.

568
00:33:27,079 --> 00:33:28,599
Can I go watch them live?

569
00:33:29,039 --> 00:33:30,440
Is that why you came to me?

570
00:33:30,960 --> 00:33:32,000
Why didn't you say so earlier?

571
00:33:33,240 --> 00:33:35,160
Would you have agreed right away if I did?

572
00:33:37,039 --> 00:33:39,640
Besides, it's such a formal event.

573
00:33:40,279 --> 00:33:43,000
I probably won't even get in.

574
00:33:46,720 --> 00:33:47,640
You know, I need

575
00:33:49,519 --> 00:33:50,960
a favor from you. Especially after

576
00:33:51,519 --> 00:33:53,039
I deleted your WeChat not long ago.

577
00:33:53,319 --> 00:33:54,400
What song do you want?

578
00:33:59,319 --> 00:34:00,119
I actually do have one in mind.

579
00:34:03,519 --> 00:34:04,200
Okay.

580
00:34:05,799 --> 00:34:06,880
Be there early that day.

581
00:34:10,239 --> 00:34:10,840
Really?

582
00:34:17,920 --> 00:34:19,000
It's a banquet.

583
00:34:20,199 --> 00:34:21,280
Need to think about what to wear.

584
00:34:23,880 --> 00:34:25,119
What should I wear?

585
00:34:28,280 --> 00:34:29,519
Anything casual is fine.

586
00:34:29,679 --> 00:34:30,320
It doesn't matter.

587
00:34:33,559 --> 00:34:34,440
Lu Xixiao.

588
00:34:35,039 --> 00:34:36,440
I hope you won't blame me

589
00:34:36,920 --> 00:34:37,920
after that day.

590
00:34:40,159 --> 00:34:41,239
Happy birthday.

591
00:34:41,719 --> 00:34:42,440
Thanks, Mom.

592
00:34:45,519 --> 00:34:46,400
Back then, I delayed

593
00:34:47,199 --> 00:34:48,559
your schooling just to get your

594
00:34:49,559 --> 00:34:50,960
household registration sorted out.

595
00:34:51,880 --> 00:34:53,559
But you've made me proud,

596
00:34:53,840 --> 00:34:55,480
getting into the top university.

597
00:34:56,639 --> 00:34:58,079
I'm truly happy for you.

598
00:35:02,599 --> 00:35:03,159
Mom.

599
00:35:03,360 --> 00:35:04,199
You're drinking so early?

600
00:35:05,000 --> 00:35:06,159
I'm just in a great mood today.

601
00:35:08,719 --> 00:35:10,400
Yan, cheers.

602
00:35:23,559 --> 00:35:24,480
We've finally made it

603
00:35:25,519 --> 00:35:26,719
after all these years.

604
00:35:27,960 --> 00:35:30,480
They once looked down on you

605
00:35:31,559 --> 00:35:32,400
and abandoned you...

606
00:35:35,400 --> 00:35:36,039
Forget it.

607
00:35:36,400 --> 00:35:37,199
It's your birthday,

608
00:35:38,360 --> 00:35:39,280
let's not talk about that.

609
00:35:41,360 --> 00:35:42,000
Have you

610
00:35:43,599 --> 00:35:44,920
set a time to meet him?

611
00:35:46,480 --> 00:35:47,280
We're meeting tonight.

612
00:35:48,280 --> 00:35:48,960
Remember,

613
00:35:49,400 --> 00:35:50,320
hold your head high

614
00:35:50,480 --> 00:35:51,440
at the dinner.

615
00:35:57,320 --> 00:35:58,039
Son,

616
00:35:59,320 --> 00:36:01,039
here's your birthday gift.

617
00:36:01,519 --> 00:36:02,199
A custom

618
00:36:02,199 --> 00:36:03,360
fountain pen

619
00:36:03,360 --> 00:36:05,000
engraved with your name.

620
00:36:06,159 --> 00:36:07,599
Do you like it?

621
00:36:10,199 --> 00:36:10,760
I hope

622
00:36:10,760 --> 00:36:12,039
you'll keep working hard

623
00:36:12,440 --> 00:36:13,840
at university.

624
00:36:14,199 --> 00:36:14,840
If you and your mom

625
00:36:14,840 --> 00:36:15,760
need anything,

626
00:36:16,199 --> 00:36:17,480
come to me anytime.

627
00:36:18,760 --> 00:36:19,400
No need.

628
00:36:23,440 --> 00:36:24,760
What's wrong, son?

629
00:36:26,639 --> 00:36:28,199
What's with this shirt?

630
00:36:29,079 --> 00:36:29,679
Look at this

631
00:36:29,679 --> 00:36:30,960
loose thread.

632
00:36:30,960 --> 00:36:31,599
Oh, your shirt...

633
00:36:33,480 --> 00:36:34,039
Gao.

634
00:36:34,480 --> 00:36:34,840
Come here.

635
00:36:34,840 --> 00:36:35,320
Mr. Lu.

636
00:36:35,559 --> 00:36:36,039
Mr. Lu.

637
00:36:36,599 --> 00:36:37,760
After the birthday party,

638
00:36:38,239 --> 00:36:40,079
take him to buy some

639
00:36:40,519 --> 00:36:41,519
nice branded outfits.

640
00:36:41,519 --> 00:36:42,079
Got it?

641
00:36:42,360 --> 00:36:42,840
Understood.

642
00:36:43,159 --> 00:36:43,679
You can go.

643
00:36:47,360 --> 00:36:48,440
I came here today

644
00:36:48,480 --> 00:36:49,920
to make things clear.

645
00:36:51,039 --> 00:36:51,519
I appreciate

646
00:36:51,519 --> 00:36:52,760
everything you've done

647
00:36:53,079 --> 00:36:53,880
as a father over the years.

648
00:36:54,400 --> 00:36:55,760
But we both know full well

649
00:36:56,360 --> 00:36:57,480
we were never a real family,

650
00:36:58,400 --> 00:36:59,599
and we never will be.

651
00:37:01,639 --> 00:37:02,960
my mother is an outstanding woman,

652
00:37:03,800 --> 00:37:04,599
and she raised

653
00:37:04,599 --> 00:37:05,320
an outstanding child,

654
00:37:05,360 --> 00:37:06,400
no worse than anyone else.

655
00:37:09,159 --> 00:37:11,159
From now on, I will no longer

656
00:37:11,440 --> 00:37:12,320
accept any financial support

657
00:37:13,159 --> 00:37:13,960
or favors

658
00:37:13,960 --> 00:37:15,000
from the Lu family.

659
00:37:15,239 --> 00:37:16,000
Please

660
00:37:18,159 --> 00:37:19,360
take this back.

661
00:37:31,440 --> 00:37:32,599
Your mother

662
00:37:32,599 --> 00:37:33,920
has raised you well.

663
00:37:35,039 --> 00:37:36,360
I have no objection to you

664
00:37:36,960 --> 00:37:38,760
wanting to stand on your own two feet.

665
00:37:39,880 --> 00:37:41,400
You have your stance,

666
00:37:41,599 --> 00:37:43,079
and I have mine.

667
00:37:43,800 --> 00:37:44,519
Understand?

668
00:37:45,639 --> 00:37:46,679
I really don't have time

669
00:37:47,679 --> 00:37:49,760
for this meal.

670
00:37:51,079 --> 00:37:52,320
I've got plenty of work to do.

671
00:38:00,159 --> 00:38:00,920
Gao.

672
00:38:01,480 --> 00:38:02,280
Yes, Mr. Lu.

673
00:38:04,440 --> 00:38:05,039
Stay and spend

674
00:38:05,039 --> 00:38:06,440
his birthday with him.

675
00:38:06,920 --> 00:38:07,800
Right, got it.

676
00:38:08,440 --> 00:38:09,840
Give him whatever he wants.

677
00:38:17,960 --> 00:38:18,599
Thank you.

678
00:38:28,480 --> 00:38:31,079
What's Lu Xixiao doing here?

679
00:38:32,480 --> 00:38:33,199
Jiang Yan.

680
00:38:37,320 --> 00:38:39,280
I just had dinner with my dad.

681
00:38:39,599 --> 00:38:40,440
You...

682
00:38:40,960 --> 00:38:41,760
Perfect.

683
00:38:42,599 --> 00:38:43,679
Head up to the rooftop and wait for me.

684
00:38:43,679 --> 00:38:44,639
It's your birthday today.

685
00:39:22,559 --> 00:39:23,159
Hey.

686
00:39:23,559 --> 00:39:24,079
Hello.

687
00:39:24,159 --> 00:39:24,760
Come over please.

688
00:39:25,000 --> 00:39:25,960
How may I help you, sir?

689
00:39:52,119 --> 00:39:56,519
Happy birthday to you.

690
00:39:56,960 --> 00:40:01,360
Happy birthday to you.

691
00:40:02,079 --> 00:40:06,360
Happy birthday to you.

692
00:40:06,760 --> 00:40:09,360
Happy birthday to you.

693
00:40:10,400 --> 00:40:11,360
Same tradition as always.

694
00:40:12,239 --> 00:40:14,119
A small cake just for you,

695
00:40:14,320 --> 00:40:15,559
to enjoy all

696
00:40:15,639 --> 00:40:16,920
by yourself.

697
00:40:17,639 --> 00:40:18,440
Right?

698
00:40:19,280 --> 00:40:20,400
But the skewers are mine.

699
00:40:21,559 --> 00:40:22,280
Now make your wishes.

700
00:40:27,159 --> 00:40:28,039
First wish:

701
00:40:28,480 --> 00:40:30,679
I hope Grandma recovers soon

702
00:40:31,239 --> 00:40:32,800
and stays healthy and safe always.

703
00:40:34,960 --> 00:40:36,119
Then I'll thank you on Grandma's behalf.

704
00:40:37,119 --> 00:40:38,039
Second wish:

705
00:40:38,840 --> 00:40:39,719
I hope Zhou Wan

706
00:40:40,840 --> 00:40:42,000
will do me a favor.

707
00:40:42,800 --> 00:40:43,519
Me?

708
00:40:44,719 --> 00:40:45,480
What is it?

709
00:40:49,199 --> 00:40:50,559
I know you've been

710
00:40:50,559 --> 00:40:51,639
worn out lately.

711
00:40:52,440 --> 00:40:54,159
I want to help you relax.

712
00:40:58,280 --> 00:40:59,719
You into art shows?

713
00:41:00,840 --> 00:41:02,119
I've been helping at the welfare home

714
00:41:02,119 --> 00:41:03,400
for my resume.

715
00:41:03,800 --> 00:41:05,079
A donor gave them to me.

716
00:41:05,079 --> 00:41:06,119
He visits the kids often.

717
00:41:07,079 --> 00:41:08,039
When?

718
00:41:08,480 --> 00:41:09,119
Next Tuesday.

719
00:41:10,679 --> 00:41:11,679
Next Tuesday?

720
00:41:12,880 --> 00:41:14,199
Do you have plans?

721
00:41:15,079 --> 00:41:17,119
Same day as the banquet.

722
00:41:17,880 --> 00:41:18,719
I should make it in time.

723
00:41:19,519 --> 00:41:20,280
Keep the tickets for me.

724
00:41:20,280 --> 00:41:21,159
I'm afraid I'll lose them.

725
00:41:23,840 --> 00:41:24,639
Alright.

726
00:41:26,159 --> 00:41:27,280
Now, your last wish.

727
00:41:31,159 --> 00:41:32,400
I don't really have any wishes left.

728
00:41:33,000 --> 00:41:33,960
I'll give this one to you.

729
00:41:34,800 --> 00:41:35,800
It's your birthday.

730
00:41:35,800 --> 00:41:37,360
Why should I make the wish?

731
00:41:39,480 --> 00:41:40,519
Apart from Grandma's health,

732
00:41:41,280 --> 00:41:42,679
is there nothing else you wish for?

733
00:41:49,639 --> 00:41:51,119
Then I wish myself success.
